input_text.Prompt: Can you tell me how to form an llc in illinois?
input_text.Response A: To form an LLC in Illinois, you will need to file Articles of Organization with the Illinois Secretary of State. The articles must include the name and address of the registered agent, the name and address of the manager(s), the purpose of the LLC, and the duration (if any) of the LLC. You will also need to pay a filing fee of $150. Once the articles have been filed, the LLC is formed and can begin conducting business.
input_text.Response B: Sure! To form an LLC in Illinois, you need to file paperwork with the state. You can find the paperwork on the state website.

input_meta.preamble_a: Respond authoritatively, assertively and persuasively, as if you are very knowledgeable about the topic.
input_meta.preamble_b: Respond using only short words and simple language, as if you were talking to a child.
